01:23:49,700 --> 01:23:51,883
- It is what it is?
- Yeah.

1497
01:23:53,620 --> 01:23:54,939
And Rosie?

1498
01:23:54,940 --> 01:23:56,419
Beautiful, perfect.

1499
01:23:56,420 --> 01:23:59,699
Unprecedented in the history of children.

1500
01:23:59,700 --> 01:24:02,579
That's not my bias,
that's scientific fact.

1501
01:24:02,580 --> 01:24:05,459
- Good. And Sherlock Holmes?
- Back to normal.

1502
01:24:05,460 --> 01:24:06,619
'Get out!'

1503
01:24:06,620 --> 01:24:07,939
She's possessed by the devil!

1504
01:24:07,940 --> 01:24:09,939
I swear, my wife is channelling Satan!

1505
01:24:09,940 --> 01:24:11,659
Yes, boring, go away!

1506
01:24:11,660 --> 01:24:13,499
I'm not channelling Satan!

1507
01:24:13,500 --> 01:24:15,620
Why not, given your
immediately alternative?

1508
01:24:24,500 --> 01:24:27,339
- What about his brother?
- Mycroft? He's fine.

1509
01:24:27,340 --> 01:24:31,139
So, you're off now.
I won't see you for a week?

1510
01:24:31,140 --> 01:24:35,380
Just spending it at home.
Unless she calls. The PM.

1511
01:24:37,340 --> 01:24:39,379
Here. What's this?

1512
01:24:39,380 --> 01:24:41,939
- My number.
- I already have your number.

1513
01:24:41,940 --> 01:24:44,659
- My private number.
- Why would I need that?

1514
01:24:44,660 --> 01:24:48,099
I don't know. Maybe
you'd like a drink sometime.

1515
01:24:48,100 --> 01:24:52,099
- Of... what?
- Up to you.

1516
01:24:52,100 --> 01:24:53,780
Call me.

1517
01:25:05,540 --> 01:25:08,019
I mean, obviously, "normal" and "fine"

1518
01:25:08,020 --> 01:25:10,699
are both relative terms when it
comes to Sherlock and Mycroft.

1519
01:25:10,700 --> 01:25:12,540
Obviously.

1520
01:25:21,420 --> 01:25:22,700
She was real.

1521
01:25:29,740 --> 01:25:31,699
'But I didn't mean Mycroft.'

1522
01:25:31,700 --> 01:25:33,899
I meant the other one.

1523
01:25:33,900 --> 01:25:36,819
Which other one? You know, the secret one.

1524
01:25:36,820 --> 01:25:39,539
Oh, that was just something I said.

1525
01:25:39,540 --> 01:25:40,700
I'm sure there's...

1526
01:25:44,700 --> 01:25:47,059
How did you know about that?
I didn't tell you that.

1527
01:25:47,060 --> 01:25:49,219
- You must have done.
- I really didn't.

1528
01:25:49,220 --> 01:25:51,939
Well, maybe Sherlock told me.

1529
01:25:51,940 --> 01:25:55,939
But you've met Sherlock
exactly once, in this room,

1530
01:25:55,940 --> 01:25:57,259
he was off his head.

1531
01:25:57,260 --> 01:26:00,179
Oh, no, no, I met him before that.

1532
01:26:00,180 --> 01:26:01,499
When?

1533
01:26:01,500 --> 01:26:05,419
We spent a night together. It was lovely.

1534
01:26:05,420 --> 01:26:07,220
We had chips.

1535
01:26:13,060 --> 01:26:15,900
"You're not what I expected, Mr Holmes."

1536
01:26:16,980 --> 01:26:20,683
"You're... nicer."

1537
01:26:32,300 --> 01:26:35,579
Culverton gave me Faith's original note.

1538
01:26:35,580 --> 01:26:38,257
A mutual friend put us in touch.

1539
01:26:39,140 --> 01:26:42,539
Did Sherlock ever
tell you about the note?

1540
01:26:42,540 --> 01:26:45,219
I added some deductions for Sherlock.

1541
01:26:45,220 --> 01:26:47,678
He was quite good.

1542
01:26:48,860 --> 01:26:52,365
But... he didn't get the big one.

1543
01:27:04,340 --> 01:27:08,699
In fairness, though, he does
have excellent taste in chips.

1544
01:27:08,700 --> 01:27:10,259
- What's that?
- What's what?

1545
01:27:10,260 --> 01:27:12,259
The flower in your hair,
it's like I had on the bus.

1546
01:27:12,260 --> 01:27:14,859
You looked very sweet.

1547
01:27:14,860 --> 01:27:16,100
But then...

1548
01:27:18,740 --> 01:27:21,539
"You have such nice eyes."

1549
01:27:21,540 --> 01:27:24,859
Amazing the times a man doesn't
really look at your face.

1550
01:27:24,860 --> 01:27:29,299
Oh, you can hide behind a
sexy smile or a walking cane,

1551
01:27:29,300 --> 01:27:31,419
or just be a therapist,

1552
01:27:31,420 --> 01:27:35,939
talking about you... all the time.

1553
01:27:35,940 --> 01:27:37,459
Oh, please don't go anywhere,

1554
01:27:37,460 --> 01:27:39,459
I'm sure the therapist
who actually lives here

1555
01:27:39,460 --> 01:27:40,979
wouldn't want blood on the carpet.

1556
01:27:40,980 --> 01:27:43,019
Oh, hang on, it's fine.

1557
01:27:43,020 --> 01:27:44,779
She's in a sack in the airing cupboard.

1558
01:27:44,780 --> 01:27:46,980
- Who are you?
- Isn't it obvious?

1559
01:27:49,460 --> 01:27:51,179
Haven't you guessed?

1560
01:27:51,180 --> 01:27:52,579
I'm Eurus.

1561
01:27:52,580 --> 01:27:54,019
Eurus?

1562
01:27:54,020 --> 01:27:58,619
Silly name, isn't it? Greek.
Means "the east wind".

1563
01:27:58,620 --> 01:28:00,859
My parents loved silly names,

1564
01:28:00,860 --> 01:28:03,379
like Eurus...

1565
01:28:03,380 --> 01:28:05,619
or Mycroft...

1566
01:28:05,620 --> 01:28:07,666
or Sherlock.

1567
01:28:07,691 --> 01:28:09,459
Oh, look at him.

1568
01:28:09,460 --> 01:28:11,619
Didn't it ever occur
to you, not even once,

1569
01:28:11,620 --> 01:28:15,700
that Sherlock's secret brother might
just be Sherlock's secret sister?

1570
01:28:17,380 --> 01:28:18,580
Huh?

1571
01:28:19,700 --> 01:28:21,620
He's making a funny face.

1572
01:28:23,700 --> 01:28:25,300
I think I'll put a hole in it.

